commit.message: sayWideCharacters() should only honour SAY_OPT_MUTE_FIRST for the first segment.
sayScreenCharacters() needs buffers that can be huge so use malooc() rather than VLAs.
The attributes argument to sayWideCharacters() can be NULL.
If the screen is too big then too many characters are written to the speech driver all at once.
Add shifted keys to the Linux screen driver's XT Key Entry table.
Add the show=yes/no parameter to the File Viewer screen driver.
Some fixes to the German contraction table (ml).

File Viewer changes:

Typing should beep.
Home and End key handlnig should be sensitive to the Control modifier.
Resolve an incorrect compiler warning about a string overread in spk_input.
Android: Add translations for the Ukranian language. (yv)
Dracut: Arch Linux uses /usr/share/brltty/ rather than /etc/brltty/.
Suppress javadoc style warnings.
Remove problematic experimental code from the Linux screen driver.
xbrlapi: Check that the (new) -w and -c options have been set.
xbrlapi: Add the -w (--write-window) and -c (--write-command) options.
Linux screen driver: Log the keyboard mode.
The Linux screen driver no longer needs to implement the GUI_APP_LIST command.
xbrlapi: Monitor changes to the WM_COMMAND window property.
Rename cmd_custom:apiEligibleCommand() to isIneligibleApiCommand().
Map SCR_KEY_ENTER to XK_Return (rather than to XK_KP_Enter).
Add support for CapsLock as a modifier key.
Ensure that there are no pending key release events in the inactive keyboard table.

Revert "Add the SpeechChanges parameter to the BrlAPI driver."

This reverts commit d60102b455feaeb0e55ca65c16ebdf810d39c966.
Not passing the GUI_APP_LIST command to the API is now handled by cmd_custom.
The Linux screen driver needs to handle the keyboard mode OFF.
Add apiEligibleCommand().
Add the -G (--gui-keyboard-table) option.
key tables: Add the assignGlobal directive.
BrlAPI: Don't forward the GUI_APP_LIST command to clients.
The MACRO and HOSTCMD commands shouldn't be forwarded to BrlAPI clients.
